## 4. Entry Point

### `InventoryBackendApplication.java`

```java
@SpringBootApplication
public class InventoryBackendApplication {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        SpringApplication.run(InventoryBackendApplication.class, args);
    }
}
```

**What happens when this runs:**
1. Spring Boot scans all packages under `com.example.inventory`
2. Finds all `@Controller`, `@Service`, `@Repository`, `@Component`, `@Configuration` classes
3. Creates instances (beans) of all these classes and wires them together
4. Starts embedded Tomcat server on port 8088
5. Hibernate connects to MySQL and creates/updates tables
6. Application is ready to accept HTTP requests

