### 16.3 `JwtUtils.java` — TOKEN FACTORY (Full Actual Code)

```java
package com.example.inventory.security;

import io.jsonwebtoken.*;
import io.jsonwebtoken.io.Decoders;
import io.jsonwebtoken.security.Keys;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.springframework.beans.factory.annotation.Value;
import org.springframework.security.core.Authentication;
import org.springframework.security.core.userdetails.UserDetails;
import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;

import javax.crypto.SecretKey;
import java.util.Date;

@Component  // ← Spring manages this class (can be @Autowired elsewhere)
public class JwtUtils {

    private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(JwtUtils.class);

    @Value("${app.jwtSecret}")
    private String jwtSecret;
    // ↑ Reads "MySuperSecretKeyForJWTTokenGenerationInSpringBootApplication12345"
    //   from application.properties
    //   This secret is used to SIGN tokens — if someone doesn't know this secret,
    //   they CANNOT forge a valid token

    @Value("${app.jwtExpirationMs}")
    private long jwtExpirationMs;
    // ↑ Reads 86400000 (24 hours in milliseconds)
    //   After this time, the token becomes INVALID and user must login again

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // PRIVATE: Creates the cryptographic signing key
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    private SecretKey getSigningKey() {
        byte[] keyBytes = Decoders.BASE64.decode(
                java.util.Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(jwtSecret.getBytes()));
        return Keys.hmacShaKeyFor(keyBytes);
        // Converts the string secret into a proper HMAC-SHA cryptographic key
        // HMAC-SHA256 = Hash-based Message Authentication Code
        // It ensures the token hasn't been tampered with
    }

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // PUBLIC: Generate a new JWT token after login
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    public String generateJwtToken(Authentication authentication) {
        UserDetails userPrincipal = (UserDetails) authentication.getPrincipal();
        // ↑ Get the authenticated user's details (email + roles)

        return Jwts.builder()
                .subject(userPrincipal.getUsername())
                // ↑ Token payload: who this token belongs to (email)

                .issuedAt(new Date())
                // ↑ When was this token created (current time)

                .expiration(new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + jwtExpirationMs))
                // ↑ When does it expire (current time + 24 hours)

                .signWith(getSigningKey())
                // ↑ Sign the token with our secret key
                //   If anyone modifies the token content, the signature won't match

                .compact();
                // ↑ Build the final token string like:
                //   "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ1c2VyQGVtYWlsLmNvbSIs..."
    }

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // PUBLIC: Extract email from an existing token
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    public String getUserNameFromJwtToken(String token) {
        return Jwts.parser()
                .verifyWith(getSigningKey())   // Verify signature matches
                .build()
                .parseSignedClaims(token)      // Parse the token
                .getPayload()
                .getSubject();                 // Extract "subject" (email)
        // If token is tampered → throws exception
        // If token is expired → throws ExpiredJwtException
    }

    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    // PUBLIC: Check if a token is valid
    // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
    public boolean validateJwtToken(String authToken) {
        try {
            Jwts.parser().verifyWith(getSigningKey()).build().parseSignedClaims(authToken);
            return true;
            // ✅ Token signature is valid AND not expired
        } catch (SecurityException e) {
            logger.error("Invalid JWT signature: {}", e.getMessage());
            // Someone tried to forge a token with a different secret
        } catch (MalformedJwtException e) {
            logger.error("Invalid JWT token: {}", e.getMessage());
            // Token format is corrupted/invalid
        } catch (ExpiredJwtException e) {
            logger.error("JWT token is expired: {}", e.getMessage());
            // Token was valid but 24 hours have passed
        } catch (UnsupportedJwtException e) {
            logger.error("JWT token is unsupported: {}", e.getMessage());
            // Token uses an algorithm we don't support
        } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {
            logger.error("JWT claims string is empty: {}", e.getMessage());
            // Empty/null token
        }
        return false;  // ❌ Token is invalid for any reason
    }
}
```

**JWT Token Structure (what's inside the token string):**
```
eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9.eyJzdWIiOiJ1c2VyQGVtYWlsLmNvbSIsImlhdCI6MTcxNzY4MzIwMCwiZXhwIjoxNzE3NzY5NjAwfQ.abc123signature

    HEADER                  PAYLOAD (Claims)                                    SIGNATURE
    ──────                  ────────────────                                    ─────────
    {                       {                                                   HMAC-SHA256(
      "alg": "HS256"         "sub": "user@email.com",  ← subject (email)         header + "." + payload,
    }                         "iat": 1717683200,        ← issued at               secretKey
                              "exp": 1717769600         ← expires at            )
                            }
```

