## 19. END-TO-END SCENARIOS

### Scenario A: First-time User Experience

```
1. User opens http://localhost:3000 → redirected to /login (no token)
2. User clicks "Register" → goes to /register
3. User fills: firstName="John", lastName="Doe", email="john@test.com", password="pass123"
4. Frontend sends POST /api/auth/signup → Backend:
   a. Validates fields (not blank, valid email)
   b. Checks email doesn't exist already
   c. Hashes "pass123" → "$2a$10$..."
   d. Creates ROLE_USER if not exists
   e. Saves user + assigns role
   f. Returns: {"message": "User registered successfully"}
5. Frontend redirects to /login
6. User enters email + password
7. Frontend sends POST /api/auth/login → Backend:
   a. Loads user by email from DB
   b. Compares BCrypt hash → matches!
   c. Generates JWT: subject="john@test.com", expires=+24h
   d. Returns: {"token":"eyJ...", "email":"john@test.com", "firstName":"John", "lastName":"Doe"}
8. Frontend stores token in localStorage
9. Frontend redirects to /dashboard
10. All future requests include: Authorization: Bearer eyJ...
```

### Scenario B: Adding a Product

```
1. User is on /products page (authenticated)
2. User clicks "Add Product" → navigates to /products/add
3. User fills: name="Laptop", description="Gaming", manufacturer="ASUS", quantity=10, price=1299.99
4. Frontend validates with Formik + Yup (client-side)
5. Frontend sends POST /api/products with JWT header → Backend:
   a. JwtFilter validates token ✓
   b. SecurityChain: user is authenticated ✓
   c. Request reaches ProductController.createProduct()
   d. @RequestBody parses JSON → Product object
   e. productRepository.save(product) → INSERT INTO products VALUES(...)
   f. Returns saved product with auto-generated ID
6. Frontend shows success toast
7. Frontend navigates to /products (list)
8. ProductList sends GET /api/products → gets updated list including new product
```

### Scenario C: Token Expired (After 24 Hours)

```
1. User has been away for 25 hours
2. User tries to view products
3. Frontend sends GET /api/products with old JWT → Backend:
   a. JwtFilter extracts token
   b. validateJwtToken() → catches ExpiredJwtException → returns false
   c. SecurityContext NOT set (user not authenticated)
   d. SecurityChain: /api/products requires authentication → user not authenticated
   e. Returns 401 Unauthorized
4. Frontend Axios interceptor catches 401
5. Frontend redirects to /login
6. User must login again to get a new token
```
